 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy governs capacity and availability planning:
 establishing baselines,
 defining thresholds,
 identifying trends,
 and driving remediation before gaps become service failures.
 The threshold values defined under this policy are provided to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Monitoring and Event Management Policy) for implementation in automated monitoring configurations;
 real-time monitoring and alerting against those thresholds is governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 not this policy.
 The services under management are those with active SLA commitments under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Service Catalog and SLA Policy).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Capacity Baseline
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall maintain a current capacity baseline across all in-scope resource categories:
 storage,
 compute,
 network bandwidth,
 and application performance.
 The Assistant IT Director shall establish the baseline from measured actuals,
 shall update the baseline no less than quarterly,
 and shall document the baseline in the System of Engagement.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Data Collection
\series default
:
 The Systems Administrator shall collect and update storage and compute utilization data.
 The Network Administrator shall collect and update network bandwidth utilization data.
 The Systems Administrator and Network Administrator shall each submit updated utilization data to the Assistant IT Director no later than the fifth (5th) business day of each quarter.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Quarterly Validation
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall validate the accuracy of the capacity baseline no less than quarterly by reconciling domain inputs against the documented baseline and correcting any discrepancies.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Knowledge Base Maintenance
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that Knowledge Base entries maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Knowledge Management Policy) that document capacity baselines,
 availability thresholds,
 or planning procedures are reviewed and updated following each quarterly baseline validation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Availability Measurement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall measure availability for all services with active SLA commitments under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The Assistant IT Director shall distinguish planned downtime from unplanned downtime in all availability measurements.
 The Assistant IT Director shall measure availability actuals against 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 SLA targets no less than monthly and shall update availability records to reflect current actuals in advance of each quarterly briefing.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Systems Administrator shall provide domain-specific availability data for systems within their domain.
 The Network Administrator shall provide domain-specific availability data for network infrastructure.
 The Systems Administrator and Network Administrator shall each submit availability data to the Assistant IT Director no later than the fifth (5th) business day of the following month.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall ensure that availability data is provided to the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 reporting processes for inclusion in service level performance reports.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Threshold Definition
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall define capacity and availability thresholds that,
 when breached,
 indicate risk to service level commitments.
 Each threshold entry shall include the resource category,
 the metric being measured,
 the threshold value,
 and the associated service or configuration item.
 The Assistant IT Director shall document threshold values in the System of Engagement and shall provide them to the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 monitoring function for implementation in automated monitoring configurations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall review threshold values no less than annually or whenever a Significant or Emergency change,
 as defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Change Management Policy),
 is executed against the service catalog or infrastructure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Forecasting and Planning
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall conduct forward-looking capacity and availability planning no less than annually.
 The Assistant IT Director shall time planning to inform the County budget cycle and shall account for known service changes,
 projected growth,
 and aging infrastructure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Where forecasting identifies a gap between projected capacity and committed service levels,
 the Assistant IT Director shall develop a remediation plan within thirty (30) calendar days of gap identification.
 The Assistant IT Director shall present any remediation plan requiring budget allocation or infrastructure change to the IT Director for approval before submission to the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 change process.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall route emergency capacity issues requiring immediate infrastructure change through the 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 Emergency change category.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.5 Issue Response
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
When monitoring under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.12"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 identifies a threshold breach,
 the Assistant IT Director shall investigate and determine whether the breach represents a transient condition or a structural capacity or availability gap.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Transient Conditions
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall document transient conditions,
 including duration and impact,
 in the System of Engagement prior to closing the associated record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Structural Gaps
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall document structural gaps in the System of Engagement.
 The Assistant IT Director shall escalate gaps that pose imminent risk to service level commitments to the remediation planning process defined in Section 6.4 immediately.
 The Assistant IT Director shall incorporate gaps that do not pose imminent risk into the next annual planning cycle under Section 6.4.
\end_layout

